         <abstract>
            <p>Let α be an algebraic integer of degree d, not 0 or a root of unity, all of whose conjugates α<sub>i</sub> are confined to a sector <tex-math>$\vert \arg z\vert \leq \theta$</tex-math>. In the paper On the absolute Mahler measure of polynomials having all zeros in a sector, G. Rhin and C. Smyth compute the greatest lower bound c(θ) of the absolute Mahler measure <tex-math>$(\prod_{i=1}^{d} \max(1, \vert\alpha_i\vert))^{1/d}$</tex-math> of α, for θ belonging to nine subintervals of <tex-math>$[0, 2\pi/3]$</tex-math>. In this paper, we improve the result to thirteen subintervals of <tex-math>$[0, \pi]$</tex-math> and extend some existing subintervals.</p>
          </abstract>
